Strong storms rumbled through the Southern Plains early on Thursday . 
  The storm system stretches from Texas up to the Great Lakes and down to North Carolina . 
  Hail of up to 4 inches in diameter smashed buildings and cars and high winds tore off roofs and trees in 12 states . 
  Storm system has the potential to be the biggest severe weather event so far this spring . 
  Tornadoes were reported on Wednesday and early Thursday in Kansas, Missouri and Oklahoma . 
  Thursday's worst weather is predicted in an area that includes Chicago, Detroit and St . 
  Louis . 
  57 million people are at an 'enhanced risk' of hail, damaging winds and tornadoes . 
 